WEBVTT

00:00.420 --> 00:02.420
Previously on Greenleaf.

00:02.427 --> 00:04.766
Any fresh libel in the paper
about us this morning, Jacob?

00:04.820 --> 00:07.354
Just this Friday feature
about churchgoers in the DA's office,

00:07.355 --> 00:09.355
Written by this Darius Nash?

00:09.380 --> 00:11.740
I really don't know
how all this is gonna end.

00:11.768 --> 00:13.848
<i>And all the side deals that he's making.</i>

00:13.881 --> 00:16.471
I can't lose half the deacon
board over a choir director.

00:16.504 --> 00:18.550
You knew I was gay.
All this has got to be about

00:18.584 --> 00:19.959
Reggie and I getting married.

00:19.992 --> 00:21.590
<i>It's a program for guys</i>

00:21.624 --> 00:23.146
who are dealing with a similar issue.

00:23.170 --> 00:25.526
<i>We wanted the bishop
to do this wedding.</i>

00:25.560 --> 00:27.958
You never would have been
my first choice.

00:27.992 --> 00:31.030
<i>Zora snuck out of the conference
and Sophia covered for her.</i>

00:31.064 --> 00:33.110
<i>I want to get baptized.</i>

00:36.087 --> 00:38.070
<i>Kevin and Charity
might be divorcing.</i>

00:38.103 --> 00:40.086
We will be seeking your guidance.

00:40.120 --> 00:41.398
Do you have a lawyer yet?

00:41.432 --> 00:43.287
When you get one, have him call me.

00:46.584 --> 00:47.831
<i>It was rated number one</i>

00:47.863 --> 00:49.751
most beautiful college in the country.

00:49.783 --> 00:51.655
I'm sure it's very beautiful.

00:52.407 --> 00:54.871
Yeah. And it says here
they have a very good

00:54.904 --> 00:56.471
religious studies program.

00:56.503 --> 00:58.331
Is that what you want to study?

00:58.839 --> 01:01.687
You already know what your major
is, sweetheart?

01:01.719 --> 01:03.126
Maybe.

01:03.160 --> 01:04.367
I don't know.

01:05.559 --> 01:07.816
It'd be so simple
to just go to college here.

01:08.439 --> 01:10.615
Would you please, please,
please just give me the money

01:10.647 --> 01:12.439
for the application fee?

01:12.471 --> 01:14.527
Well, Rhodes might be
the simplest option, sweetheart,

01:14.551 --> 01:16.951
but that doesn't make it the best one.

01:16.984 --> 01:18.264
Are you trying to get rid of me?

01:18.295 --> 01:19.894
No.

01:19.928 --> 01:21.910
I just know college is a big choice.

01:21.944 --> 01:24.086
I want you to think big, honey.

01:24.120 --> 01:26.040
Going to the most beautiful
campus in the country

01:26.071 --> 01:27.670
seems pretty big.

01:27.704 --> 01:29.910
Well, life is more than beauty.

01:34.168 --> 01:37.974
You got a lot of spice
this early, baby.

01:38.008 --> 01:39.446
Parentals.

01:39.480 --> 01:41.626
- I'm making eggs.
- No, thank you.

01:41.659 --> 01:43.319
I'll go with a yogurt.

01:43.351 --> 01:45.943
So, here's the thing.

01:45.975 --> 01:47.222
Yes?

01:47.256 --> 01:49.110
I would like to have a reexamination

01:49.143 --> 01:51.447
of this "no dating" policy.

01:51.479 --> 01:52.759
It's not a "no dating" policy.

01:52.791 --> 01:56.151
It's a "no reprobate thug" policy.

01:56.183 --> 01:59.127
Isaiah's not a thug.
He's in a gospel group.

01:59.159 --> 02:01.174
- He's Christian.
- He's a Christian thug.

02:01.208 --> 02:03.286
That's a thing.
Now, your father used to be one

02:03.320 --> 02:06.263
before I straightened him out.

02:06.295 --> 02:08.150
Just give him another chance.

02:08.184 --> 02:09.110
No.

02:09.144 --> 02:10.582
One week with that boy,

02:10.615 --> 02:12.534
and you were lying and sneaking around.

02:12.568 --> 02:13.791
Don't make him pay for my mistakes.

02:13.815 --> 02:15.734
I'm the one with the problem here.

02:15.767 --> 02:16.886
What are you thinking?

02:16.920 --> 02:19.191
What... what are you thinking?

02:21.208 --> 02:23.094
I would like to invite him

02:23.128 --> 02:25.142
to Sophia's birthday party.

02:25.175 --> 02:27.158
No lying, no sneaking.

02:27.191 --> 02:29.239
Just good, clean Christian fun.

02:30.712 --> 02:31.712
Two peas in a pod.

02:35.191 --> 02:37.431
As long as you don't leave the premises.

02:37.463 --> 02:39.959
Look at us... learning, growing.

02:39.991 --> 02:41.942
I got to say, you two,

02:41.976 --> 02:45.078
I am proud to be part of the process.

02:47.544 --> 02:50.326
And, as stipulated
in our memorandum of understanding,

02:50.359 --> 02:52.535
Mr. Satterlee will be responsible

02:52.567 --> 02:54.390
for his debts incurred
during the marriage?

02:54.423 --> 02:56.150
That's correct.

02:56.184 --> 02:58.486
And the same for Miss Greenleaf?

02:58.519 --> 03:01.398
Yes, and you'll find that all broken
down in today's addendum.

03:01.432 --> 03:04.694
And finally, in the matter
of Nathan Satterlee,

03:04.727 --> 03:07.158
both parties agree to joint custody?

03:07.192 --> 03:09.656
Yeah, but we have one question.

03:10.263 --> 03:14.358
It looks like I'll be going
to Nashville fairly regularly,

03:14.391 --> 03:16.406
more often than I originally thought.

03:16.440 --> 03:17.471
Is that right?

03:17.504 --> 03:20.118
Kevin, what Charity might suggest

03:20.151 --> 03:21.622
might actually be a blessing.

03:21.655 --> 03:23.190
Remember...

03:23.223 --> 03:25.758
look for God's hand at work
in what you fear the most.

03:25.791 --> 03:27.926
- I'm looking.
- I just wanted to know

03:27.960 --> 03:29.960
if we could change
the visitation language

03:29.961 --> 03:32.072
to make more space for flexibility.

03:32.106 --> 03:33.673
So you can run off with Jabari?

03:33.705 --> 03:35.912
I'm not running off with Jabari.

03:35.946 --> 03:37.961
Kevin, I'm pursuing my career.

03:37.993 --> 03:39.128
With another man in Nashville.

03:39.152 --> 03:40.495
Well, what do you care?

03:43.114 --> 03:44.456
Why don't we stop for today?

